<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11938&amp;p=135296#p135296"><![CDATA[
This patch over here brings up an interesting scenario for some NES games.  Would it be technically possible to save a game almost in the same way as a save state?  Maniac Mansion and Crystalis sorta do that, since you can (almost) save anytime, anywhere, and it keeps your exact position and everything.  But would that be harder to implement than a normal save that keeps track of fewer variables, and not as accurately?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6132">OneCrudeDude</a> — Mon Oct 20, 2014 5:51 pm</p><hr />
